                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.77/740</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-22T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 22, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>320. War Department official responsible for PGC matters connected with operation
                    of Iranian railway states that in view of information contained in your 350 May
                    19, negotiations in connection with American participation in the proposed
                    railway agreement may be considered as having terminated. Since the Department
                    has been acting merely as a negotiating agent for the War Department in this
                    matter, you should consult with General Connolly as to the best method of
                    bringing the decision to the attention of British and possibly Soviet
                    authorities in Tehran. You may also in your discretion inform the Iranian
                    authorities although it is understood they have not made any direct approach in
                    the matter to the Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
